success.question_text: If together they walked 48 kilometres, how much further than Jenson did Lachlan walk?

stimulus_2.text: Lachlan walked three times as far as Jenson.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Don’t rush into answering a question. Take time to think.

stimulus_2.text:
The average age of five children was 7.

The ages of four of the children were 5, 9, 8 and 5.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

To find an average add the numbers together and divide by however many numbers have been added.

stimulus_1.text:
Consecutive whole numbers are numbers in order such as 16, 17 and 18.

The product of three consecutive odd numbers is 105.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Consecutive whole numbers are increasing by one. Consecutive even numbers have a difference of two; consecutive odd numbers also have a difference of two.

Tip

Sometimes the correct answer can be found by checking each of the choices given in the question.

success.question_text: How much does he save by buying them in packs rather than separately?

stimulus_2.text: Mugs can be bought for $5.95 each or in packs of six for $35.00. Wayne wants to buy a dozen of the mugs.

success.question_text: What fraction of the shape is shaded?
If Ayano provided $12 000, how much money was there altogether?

stimulus_2.text: When Ayano and Yvonne started their business, Ayano provided 60% of the money.

stimulus_1.text: In this number square, the rows and columns add up to the given totals. Some of the entries are missing.

Tip

Make sure that you read all the given information carefully.

stimulus_1.text: In this number square, the rows and columns add up to the given totals. Some of the entries are missing.

review_5.column_1_text:
Tip

The total of the sums of the rows and the total of the sums of the columns of a table should be the same. For example, in this question the total of the sums of the columns is also 127.

success.question_text: What is the smallest possible number of lollies in the bag?

stimulus_2.text:
A bag of lollies is to be shared among a group of boys.

If the lollies are shared between two boys there will be one lolly left over.

If the lollies are shared between three boys, there will be one lolly left over.

If the lollies are shared between five boys, there will be one lolly left over.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

A common multiple of two numbers can be found by multiplying the numbers. If the two numbers have no factors in common, apart from one, then this multiple will be the lowest common multiple.

success.question_text: Which number should be left out so that the average of the remaining numbers is 7?

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

To find an average add the numbers together and divide by however many numbers have been added.

stimulus_2.text: The table shows the ages of Margot, her sister (Rachael) and her mother (Dorothy).

choice_1.label: Rachael is twice the age of Margot.

choice_2.label: Margot's age is 25% of Dorothy's age.

choice_3.label: The sum of Margot's age and Rachael's age is less than Dorothy's age.

choice_4.label: Rachael's age is halfway between Margot's age and Dorothy's age.

stimulus_2.text:
A survey was conducted to find the population of a holiday town in three months of the year.
In November, the population was 6000.
In January the population had increased by 50% since November.
In March the population had decreased by 50% since January.

success.question_text: How many cows are in the paddock on the hill?

stimulus_2.text: A farm has 120 cattle, three-fifths are cows and the rest are calves. All of the cattle are in two paddocks, some in the paddock on the hill and some in the paddock beside the river. Of the cattle in the paddock on the hill, one-quarter are calves. Two-thirds of the cows are in the paddock by the river.

Tip

success.question_text: How many different possible sums are there for the three numbers on each arm?

stimulus_1.text: The numbers 1, 3, 5, 7 and 9 are to be placed in the squares that make up this cross, one number in each square, so that the three numbers along each arm add to the same number.

review_5.column_1_text:
Tip

Always consider what the question is asking and don’t try to find additional information that isn’t required. For example in this question, it was not necessary to find the three sums. You just needed to know how many there were.
